Avg Price Sheet 17

1. Right Click on Sales and select Duplicate. Change the name of the sheet to Average Price

 

2.Remove Sales and YoY Sales from the Row shelf

3. Let the date dimension be there in the column shelf



4. Drag and drop Average price  Measure to the Row shelf . Rt click and from Under Marks card select Bar . Select Average Price click on the down arrow and select Measure, Average. In the mark shelf click the drop-down list and select bar.




5. Drag and drop YoY Average Sales calculated field to the Rt side of Avg Price when you see dotted line drop the YoY Average Price .



6. In the column shelf Rt click the YoY AvgPrice and select Mark Type to Line



7. Select Legend Click on title select  down arrow and select Edit colors, select Average Price ,Green Color and for YoY Average Price select Automatic, Yellow Color



8. Select YoY Average Price  in the Row Shelf Select Format ,Axis ,Numbers, Percentage and Decimal Place 0.





9. Select YoY Avg price right axis  click on the axis under Edit Axis  and erase the title




10. Select Average price left axis  right click on the axis , Edit Axis , in Range select Fixed and enter 0 under Fixed start and erase the title



11. Select the Title and rt select Edit Title ,Erase the text and type Avg Price Change the font to Tableau Semi bold , Font size to 10 , Font Color Black ,Alignment left.



12. Click on YoY Vol in the row shelf hold control button and drag and drop it in the text box. Right click YoY Vol  select format ,pane, Numbers , Percentages and Decimal places 0.
